'''''lemin''''' is a [[Qenya]] word meaning "five".<ref>{{PE|12}}</ref><ref name=VT>{{VT|48a}}, p. 20 (note 17)</ref>

[[J.R.R. Tolkien|Tolkien]] also suggested the form ''lempe'' ("five"),<ref>{{PE|11}}, p. 53</ref> but in later manuscripts emended that form to ''lemin''.<ref name=VT/><ref>{{PE|14}}, pp. 49, 82</ref>
